args:
The moment I was old enough to hold a thought
for myself, I was summoned to the court. It was
my first audience with Lady Amaterasu, and she
spoke to me with great gentleness and care.
Hear me, Izumo. As my emissary,\nyou will be granted two powers.
The first will permit you to come to\nTakamagahara and hear my voice.
I can never remember what she said after that.\nNo matter how many times I dream of that day,\nLady Amaterasu's words are always cut short.
I'm sure it's because I've lost the second power.\nMy dreams must be telling me there's nothing\nI can do anymore.

It's a horrid dream, and I can't help but wonder if
the vestiges of Oki left within me are making me
suffer it as some twisted form of revenge.
Honestly, I...I just don't know what to do.
Huh? I'm...all right. But where am I?
You're in a village some distance from the\npalace. One of us found you at the foot of\na cliff and brought you here.
Ah, I see. Thank you very much.\nBut if I may ask, how fares the palace?
I was forced to flee after it was overtaken\nby insurgents. Has the violence spread to\nthis area yet?
Goodness, we haven't heard a thing!\nNow I'm even MORE worried about you!
Now that Lady Amaterasu has passed,\nwe would never be able to recover if\nsomething were to happen to you.
So please stay here and rest until the\nentire situation is settled.
While I appreciate your concern, I am\nunworthy of it as I am now. I must leave\nbefore I trouble you any further.
Please, I beg of you! Stay here until\nthe chaos has passed!
You'll be safe here, but who knows what\nmight happen if you leave?!
Well, I suppose it would be rude of me\nto turn you down now... In that case,\nI accept your gracious offer. Thank you.

But I refuse to simply lay about when
you've done so much to help me. There
must be something I can do to assist
your village, so please name it.
Also, once the uproar in the palace has\nsubsided, I'm certain I can provide you\nwith a suitable reward for your assistance.

Your health and safety is enough of a
reward for us, emissary. However, if you
are truly set on helping us, there is one
thing you might be able to do...
Our village is desperate for rain.\nWill you call some forth?
We've been suffering a terrible drought,\nand our entire harvest is now on the\nverge of failure.
We've heard that your power can reach\nheaven and change the weather, so please\nuse it to save our village!
That may have been possible when Lady\nAmaterasu was still here, but now...
(I can't very well say it's impossible when\nthey're begging me like this.)
I understand. I will do what I can, though\nI caution you not to expect much.
(The villagers have all gathered around.\nTheir hopes are resting on me, but...)
(Well, I have to do my best. I know the\nrainmaking ritual by heart, so maybe\nthere's still a chance it might work.)
Dragons of heaven! Dragons of earth!\nDragons of all! Hear my humble plea!
May the great raindragon hear this cry\nand send a blessing from the heavens!
My ritual failed... I am so sorry.
Do not anguish, emissary. It's quite\nunderstandable that such a thing might\nhappen given your current circumstances.
We're just grateful you tried, especially\nconsidering the state you're in.
It is wholly my fault that this happened.\nI cannot apologize enough for being\nunable to meet your expectations.
Everyone was counting on me, and I\ncouldn't do anything. I'm useless!
I can't fight like a Wyrmclan leader, I can't\ngrant people's wishes... I don't even know\nwhat I'm supposed to do anymore.
Just do what you can! Take any crap life\nthrows at you and GIVE IT YOUR AAAALL!
Yep! It's your old pal Yuki! I haven't seen\nyou since that big clan meeting, Izumo.\nGlad to see you looking sharp.
It is a pleasure to see you, Lady Yukimura.\nEr, but why are you here?
I'm looking for you, of course! Thought\nmaybe the Mukuroshu found you and\nKSSSSHK! So I'm glad to see you're okay.

After everything went crazy at the palace,
Kicho let all us Wyrmclan leaders know
what happened, including the fact you'd
gone missing.

Anyway, I was able to move out the
quickest, so here I am. And buddy,
lemme tell ya, I've been worried sick
about you in more ways than one!

Anyway, the folks back at the palace are
still in a helluva pickle. We haven't found
the main Mukuroshu guy, and we don't
even know what they even came for.
And while it's good that you're okay, the\nother clan leaders are all tied up and I\nhave ZERO idea what to do next.
Phew, I'm glad you understaâ€”HEY!\nAre you even listening to me?!\nYou're just staring off into space!
Nope. Totally not listening at all.\nTime to pull out all the stops...
HEY! IZUMO! ANYONE HOME IN THEEERE?!
Gya! Stop poking my cheeks! What is it?!\nWhat do you want?!
I want you to come back from la-la land\nand LISTEN to me, ya dope! I have a plan.
And that plan is that you and me stay\nhere for a bit! Great, right?

We don't know where the enemy is or what
they're thinkingâ€”and until we do, it's way
too dangerous to go charging back to the
palace.
Luckily, the villagers here are happy\nto have you, so let's just accept their\nhospitality and see what happens.
In the meantime, you can count on me\nto keep you safe. Sounds good, right?
Er...if you that's what you wish.
Your decision-making has to be much\nbetter than mine, seeing as I can't do\nanything anymore.
